<br>
Ahh, well - I can understand your confusion my dimunitive friend. First, you are correct! EQoA does in fact take place entirely on Antonica, which is called by the people of that time, Tunaria. <br>
<br>
In fact, the *Tunar* is the foundation of all trade, as it is the only coin used throughout the realm.<br>
<br>
Now then... Many of the names used are very similar to the place names we know from *our* time in Norrath. For example, the Elves, though still technically one race, live in two distinct towns. &quot;Fayspires&quot; is the home of what you would call &quot;High Elves&quot;; Paladins, Clerics, Wizards, Enchanters, and Magicians. &quot;Telethin&quot; is the home of what you would call &quot;Wood Elves&quot;; Rogues, Rangers, Druids, Warriors. These towns are near one another geographically, separated by a stretch of road, approximately 5 miles long.<br>
<br>
Clik'Anon is very similar sounding to Ak'Anon, Halas is still Halas, Neriak is Neriak. <br>
<br>
One could argue that they didn't exactly go buck wild with creativity here, but it can also be argued that the place names we know are merely evolutions of the earlier (EQoA) place names. /shrug.<br>
<br>
