<br>
Klik'Anon (and Mordheim) are clearly colonies from the homeland to the east. Why they were established and then abandoned is unknown at this time. In the case of Mordheim, we can assume it's because Lady Vox slew the dwarves. Klik'Anon was almost certainly established by gnomish mariners upon landfall on Tunaria (you said it was north along the coast from Freeport, right?), probably established before Freeport was founded. Any number of reasons could have lead to its abandonment, including King Ak'Anon calling the colonists home during the High Elven diaspora and its related turmoil on Faydwer.<br>
<br>
